# Deployment Walkthrough: Render (Backend) + Vercel (Frontend)

I've reverted the Vercel-specific backend configuration so that your Express app is optimized to deploy directly on Render as a standard background service, while the frontend remains fully compatible with Vercel!

## What Was Changed
- **`backend/server.js`**: Removed the Vercel serverless condition and export so the server naturally calls `app.listen()` and works beautifully on Render.
- **`backend/package.json`**: Changed the `"start"` script to `node server.js` to prevent the app from crashing on Render if the local `.env` file isn't uploaded.
- **Removed `backend/vercel.json`**: This file is no longer needed since the backend won't be hosted on Vercel.

## How to Deploy

Follow these exact steps to deploy your full stack application.

### 1. Deploy the Backend on Render
1. Go to your Render Dashboard and create a new **Web Service**.
2. Connect your `Music-SoundLink` GitHub repository.
3. In the configuration:
   - **Root Directory**: `backend`
   - **Environment**: `Node`
   - **Build Command**: `npm install`
   - **Start Command**: `npm start`
4. Expand the **Environment Variables** section and add all your backend secrets (e.g., `MONGO_URI`, `CLOUDINARY_URL`, `JWT_SECRET`, etc.).
5. Click **Create Web Service**.
6. Once deployed, Render will provide a live URL (e.g., `https://music-soundlink-api.onrender.com`). **Copy this URL**.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Make sure to update the `SERVER_URL` environment variable on Render to match your new Render URL so the `keepAlive` ping functions properly!

### 2. Deploy the Frontend on Vercel
1. Go to your Vercel Dashboard and click **Add New... > Project**.
2. Import the `Music-SoundLink` GitHub repository.
3. In the "Configure Project" screen:
   - **Framework Preset**: Select `Vite`.
   - **Root Directory**: Click "Edit" and select the `frontend` folder.
   - **Environment Variables**: Add an environment variable named `VITE_BACKEND_URL` and paste the backend URL you copied from Render (e.g., `VITE_BACKEND_URL=https://music-soundlink-api.onrender.com`).
4. Click **Deploy**.

## Verification
- Your frontend will go live on Vercel and seamlessly connect to your Render backend via the `VITE_BACKEND_URL`.
- Local development (`npm run dev`) remains unchanged and will continue to work perfectly.

> [!TIP]
> After deploying, don't forget to add your new Vercel frontend URL to the CORS allowed origins array in `backend/server.js` if you haven't already!
